HEADWORD: Dhole
<hw>Dhole</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
fierce, wild dog (<spn>Canis Dukhunensis</spn>), found in the mountains
of India. It is remarkable for its propensity to hunt the tiger and
other wild animals in packs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

